 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic>T</italic> is the deviation in global surface temperature from pre-industrial values, 
 <italic>c</italic> is the thermal capacity specific heat capacity of the Earth’s surface, 
 <italic>F</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>d</italic>
 </sub> is the net downward flux of radiation absorbed at the planet’s surface (which depends on the opacity of CO
 <sub>2</sub>), 
 <italic>σ</italic> is the Stefan-Boltzmann constant, and 
 <italic>a</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>E</italic>
 </sub> is the Earth’s surface area. Full details are provided in 
 <xref ref-type="supplementary-material" rid="pcbi.1007000.s001">S1 Text</xref>.
</p>
